ce:section.ce:para:
From the observations, we can conclude that under laser excitation wavelength of 495 nm and laser excitation wavelength of 560 nm, the green colour showed the viable cells (due to the action of calcein-AM), and red colour showed the dead cells (due to the action of propidium iodide). From the qualitative visualization and analysis (Fig. 6
                        ), it suggests cell viability did not alter or decrease over concentration after 24 h of treatment. These results suggest that UC-CDs did not decrease the viable cell count (Fig. 7
                        ) over the dead cells and possess an image-tracking ability. The percentage of viable cells under treatment with UC-CDs has been calculated with the ImageJ software. The control set has been compared with the treated UC-CDs. No significant decrease in viable cell count in human glial cells SVG p12 was observed under treatment with varying concentrations of U–C/CDs.
